The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Corporate Briefs

 Indiabulls Financial Services Ltd has posted an increase of 59.19 per cent in net profit at Rs 30.63 crore for the quarter ended September 30 against Rs 19.24 crore for the same quarter last year. The total income of the company increased 27.56 per cent to Rs 69.56 crore from Rs 54.53 crore in the corresponding quarter a year ago, the company has informed the Bombay Stock Exchange. The board of the company has declared a dividend of 5 per cent on 99.66 lakh cumulative, redeemable, non-convertible preference shares of face value of Rs 300 each, and 115 lakh cumulative, redeemable, convertible preference shares, it added.

 Venus Remedies has posted an increase of over two fold in net profit at Rs 7.06 crore for the quarter ended September 30 from Rs 3.43 crore in the same period last year. The total income of the company increased 77.77 per cent to Rs 36.64 crore for the quarter ended September 30 against Rs 20.61 crore for the corresponding period a year ago, the company has informed the Bombay Stock Exchange.

 Silverline Technologies Ltd has signed a strategic joint venture agreement with US-based Creative Infocity Inc to develop business process outsourcing and IT infrastructure facilities in Gandhinagar. The JV, to be operated by Silverline Technologies, entails developing BPO and IT infrastructure facilities in around 5 lakh square feet at Infocity in Gandhinagar.

 California Software Company Ltd will issue 5.55 lakh shares to the promoters of Intatech Infosolutions Pvt Ltd on a preferential basis for over Rs 5 crore at Rs 90 per share. The EGM also authorised the board to create, issue and allot 94.50 lakh fully convertible debentures of Rs 10 each for cash on a preferential basis to Hong Kong-based Kemoil Ltd.

 Bank of India would open 55 branches across the country and target a business of Rs 2,00,000 crore by the end of this fiscal, chairman and managing director M. Balachandran said.

 Kotak Mahindra Old Mutual Life Insurance Limited has entered into referral bancassurance partnership with Murshidabad District Central Cooperative Bank Ltd. The partnership will enable Kotak Life Insurance to tap the customer base of the bank in Murshidabad and cater to the semi-urban and rural customers of the region.

 Liberty Shoes has received an order worth of Rs 100 crore from Schhfabrik Van Elten of Germany to supply it safety shoes in the next three years. Liberty will provide Van Elten 300,000 to 500,000 pairs of safety shoes per annum in the next three years. 

